proot: proot (chroot, mount --bind, and binfmt_misc without any privilege)
proot:
proot: PRoot is a user-mode implementation of chroot, mount --bind,
proot: and binfmt_misc, that means users don't need any privilege or
proot: setup to use an arbitrary directory as the new root
proot: file-system, to make files accessible somewhere else in the
proot: file-system hierarchy, and to execute programs built for
proot: another CPU architecture transparently through QEMU.  PRoot
proot: relies on ptrace, an unprivileged system-call available in
proot: every Linux kernels.
proot: Home: http://proot.me
